messages.message: The "export annotations" works and gives me a bunch of ibmls - - are there customer docs for injecting ibmls?
For my purposes, the ibmls are fine though.
Ah great. So the problem is almost definitely that the required schema for ocr golds wasn’t what was present on that annotator project.

Maybe we could add a frontend check that shows an error before making the export attempt if the gold selection is made without the schema that matches.... the trickyness of having user-definable schemas.....
the annotator docs also don’t have any info about exporting :slightly_smiling_face: @Ted.
maybe cleaning up Annotator export / docs should be a short Q1 task.
docs would have helped even if the UI wasn’t as good about a user-defined schema being missing.
That makes sense to me—rolled up into de-betafying it
Annotator has no backend logic so should be simple to de beta
